oc:kn_01a955b5 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating 50+ ad variations with the same structure but different data" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use AI video generators when you need templated, data-driven variations at scale — use Remotion instead for deterministic, pixel-perfect output." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI generators produce unique output each time, making it impossible to maintain brand consistency across hundreds of variations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3bff89be a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before starting any generative ad creative production" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before generating, confirm: target platform dimensions, whether text must render in-image, whether voiceover is needed, and whether output must be deterministic (template) or exploratory (AI-gen)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These four parameters determine which tool category and specific tool to use, preventing wasted generations." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8c96cbe5 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When combining a silent video with a separately generated voiceover track" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "bash" ;
    oc:directiveContent "ffmpeg -i video.mp4 -i voiceover.mp3 -c:v copy -c:a aac output.mp4" ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is the standard command for merging audio and video streams without re-encoding the video." .

oc:kn_ac76fd44 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating ad images with baked-in text" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Ideogram has ~90% text rendering accuracy vs ~30% for most tools — always use Ideogram when text must be legible inside the image (headlines, logos, CTAs)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Poor text rendering makes ads look unprofessional and can render headlines unreadable." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ae15925c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scaling ad creative production" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Generate hero creative with AI image/video tools (exploratory, high quality). 2. Identify winning creative patterns from performance data. 3. Build React templates in Remotion based on winners. 4. Batch render variations from product/headline/CTA data. 5. Iterate — use AI for new angles, Remotion for scale." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_b9c16cad a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When budgeting ad creative production" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cost for 100 ad variations: ~$1-6 for static images, ~$225 for 100×15-sec AI videos, ~$0 for Remotion-rendered templated videos (self-hosted). A hybrid of 10 hero AI videos + 90 Remotion templates costs ~$22." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Understanding cost profiles enables choosing the right tool mix for the budget." .

oc:kn_cb4404c0 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When producing video ads with voiceover" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For voice + video workflows: write ad script first, generate voiceover, then either use a native-audio video generator (Veo/Sora/Seedance) or layer the voice track onto silent video (Runway/Remotion) with ffmpeg." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Separating script → voice → video gives more control over each element and enables re-recording voice without reshooting." .

oc:kn_cc5ea5f6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating multiple ad images that must look like the same brand/product" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use multi-image reference features in Flux (up to 8 refs) or Ideogram (up to 3 style refs) to maintain product/brand consistency across ad variations." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Flux supports up to 8 reference images for consistent identity, Ideogram supports up to 3 style references — specify reference images explicitly when brand/product consistency is required across variations." .

oc:kn_d3bbe0aa a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When producing ads at scale (50+ variations)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use a hybrid approach: generate hero creative with AI (Nano Banana, Flux, Veo) for exploration, then build templates in Remotion for batch variations at scale." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI generators excel at creative exploration; Remotion excels at deterministic, brand-perfect batch production. Combining both yields quality + scale." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ea4c05f2 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating ad images for specific platforms" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always include exact platform dimensions in image generation prompts (e.g., 1080x1080 for Meta Feed, 1080x1920 for Stories/Reels) to avoid post-generation cropping." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Incorrect aspect ratios require cropping or resizing, degrading quality and potentially cutting off important visual elements." .

